        <updateDate>2025-03-14T17:45:15Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No Foreign Gifts Act of 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill prohibits an institution of higher education (IHE) from receiving federal education funds if the&amp;nbsp;IHE&amp;nbsp;receives gifts from certain countries.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Specifically, the bill prohibits an IHE from receiving a gift from (1) China, Russia, North Korea, or Iran; or (2) a country that has provided material support to a foreign terrorist organization, as determined by the Department of State.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The bill also requires an IHE, as a condition of eligibility for federal education funds, to report any offer of a gift from such a foreign country.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
